CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 17, 1961, pg. 6A reads: "Gift For Potentate - Standing, left to right: Noble John W. Goggins, Deputy Imperial Promotional Director; Noble Clarence R. Queen, Illustrious Potentate; Noble Marshall S. Johnson, Imperial Captain of the Guard, and Noble William Fitzpatrick, PP, and Daughters Natalie Mucker and Fitzpatrick of Detroit's Marracci Temple, were photographed as Noble Queen received a gift, during the Potentate's Ball, recently, in Pittsburgh."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of six Shriners, from left: John W. Goggins, Clarence R. Queen, Marshall S. Johnson, William Fitzpatrick, Natalie Mucker, and Mrs. William Fitzpatrick, gathered on stage with Bobby Jones band during the Potentate Ball
